Description: # tiptapy
        Library that generates HTML output from JSON export of tiptap editor
        
        ``` {.sourceCode .python}
        import tiptapy
        
        s = """
        
        {
          "type": "doc",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "blockquote",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Readability counts."
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "link",
                          "attrs": { "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zen_of_Python" }
                        }
                      ],
                      "text": "Zen of Python"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text", "text": " By "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "bold"
                        }
                      ],
                      "text": "Tom Peters"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
        """
        
        out = tiptapy.to_html(s)
        print(out)
        ```
        
        ``` {.sourceCode .html}
        <blockquote>
          <p>Readability counts.</p>
          <p>
              <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zen_of_Python">Zen of Python</a> By 
              <strong>Tom Peters</strong>
          </p>
        </blockquote>
        ```
        
